title: New Jersey 2007 - 2008 High Resolution Orthophotography 5000 foot Tile Index (rev. 2009)
name: New Jersey 2007 - 2008 High Resolution Orthophotography 5000 foot Tile Index (rev. 2009)
description:
These 5000 foot tile index polygons define the boundaries of individual orthophoto image files produced for the New Jersey Orthophoto Mapping Program 2007-2008. The tile scheme is in New Jersey State Plane coordinates, NAD83, in units of US Survey feet.

This index is the same as the index for the 2002 - 2003 New Jersey Orthophoto Mapping Program, except for the addition of one tile in Salem County.

The index was revised in 2009, with an added attribute to indicate tiles redelivered in 2009. For four urban areas (Newark, Jersey City, Atlantic City, Trenton), tiles were reprocessed with added, off-axis imagery that was flown in 2007 and 2008  on the same dates as the other flightlines. Three additional tiles, one in West Windsor Township, Mercer County, one in Warren Township and Green Brook Township, Somerset County, and one in West Milford Township, Passaic County, were reprocessed to eliminate image processing errors in the original delivery.

author.source: NJ Office of Information Technology, Office of GIS
